# CIMTool code owners
#
# Every pull request requires an approving review from a maintainer.
# This is enforced by the "Protected branches" ruleset:
#
#     Require a pull request before merging
#       -> Require review from Code Owners
#
# Code owners must hold write access to cimug-org/CIMTool. The
# cimtool-maintainers team holds the write role on this repository.
# See GOVERNANCE.md for the distinction between the Committer and
# Maintainer roles: write access alone does not confer merge authority.
#
# IMPORTANT: GitHub reads this file from the BASE branch of a pull
# request, not from master. Because contributions target the current
# release branch, this file must exist on that branch. Commit it to
# master, then back-merge into the current release-* branch. A release
# branch cut before this file existed will not enforce code owner
# review until the file reaches it.
#
# The last matching pattern takes precedence. Add narrower path rules
# below the catch-all, never above it.

* @cimug-org/cimtool-maintainers
